hpnicfNS.name: hpnicfNS

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfNS.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the configuration and status information of network traffic statistics. It classifies the IP packets by source IP address, source port, destination IP address, destination port, protocol, ToS and input interface, counts the octets and packets, and sends the statistic information to the specific collector.

hpnicfNSActiveTime.name: hpnicfNSActiveTime
hpnicfNSActiveTime.description: The stream will be aged when the active time of this stream exceeds this value. This object is in minute.

hpnicfNSInactiveTime.name: hpnicfNSInactiveTime
hpnicfNSInactiveTime.description: The stream will be aged when the inactive time of this stream exceeds this value. This object is in second.

hpnicfNSVersion.name: hpnicfNSVersion
hpnicfNSVersion.description: The version of the exported packet, which describes the format of the exported packet. It should export version 5 and version 8 when this object is 5, but it should export version 9 only when the value of this object is 9.

hpnicfNSAsType.name: hpnicfNSAsType
hpnicfNSAsType.description: The number of autonomous system (AS). This object can be origin or peer.

hpnicfNSTemplateRefreshRate.name: hpnicfNSTemplateRefreshRate
hpnicfNSTemplateRefreshRate.description: This object specifies the refresh rate in number of exported packets.

hpnicfNSTemplateTimeout.name: hpnicfNSTemplateTimeout
hpnicfNSTemplateTimeout.description: This object specifies the timeout rate in minutes.

hpnicfNSExportVlanOrIfIndex.name: hpnicfNSExportVlanOrIfIndex
hpnicfNSExportVlanOrIfIndex.description: This object describes the interface index at the exported packet. It can be interface index or vlan id according to the product.

hpnicfNSProcessSlotTable.name: hpnicfNSProcessSlotTable
hpnicfNSProcessSlotTable.description: This table describes the board which can enable network traffic statistics at the switch or router.

hpnicfNSProcessSlot.name: hpnicfNSProcessSlot
hpnicfNSProcessSlot.description: This object describes all boards which can processes network traffic statistics at the switch or router.

hpnicfNSExportConfigTable.name: hpnicfNSExportConfigTable
hpnicfNSExportConfigTable.description: This table describes the configuration of the exported packets.

hpnicfNSAggregationType.name: hpnicfNSAggregationType
hpnicfNSAggregationType.description: The aggregation type. v5Statistics type counts IP packets which have same source IP address, destination IP address, source port, destination port, protocol, ToS, input interface, output interface. AS type counts IP packets which have same source AS, destination AS, input interface and output interface. destinationPrefix type counts IP packets which have same destination AS, output interface, destination mask and destination prefix. sourcePrefix type counts IP packets which have same source AS, input interface, source mask and source prefix. protocolPort type counts IP packets which have same protocol, source port and destination port. prefix type counts IP packets which have same source AS, destination AS, input interface, output interface, source mask, source prefix, destination mask, destination prefix. tosAS type counts IP packets which have same tos, source AS, destination AS, input interface and output interface. tosDestinationPrefix type counts IP packets which have same tos, destination AS, output interface, destination mask and destination prefix. tosProtocolPort type counts IP packets which have same tos, protocol, source port and destination port. tosSourcePrefix type counts IP packets which have same tos, source AS, input interface, source mask and source prefix. tosPrefix type counts IP packets which have same tos, source AS, destination AS, input interface, output interface, source mask, source prefix, destination mask, destination prefix. prefixPort type counts IP packets which have same tos, input interface, output interface, source mask, source prefix, destination mask, destination prefix, source port and destination port.

hpnicfNSHostIPAddr.name: hpnicfNSHostIPAddr
hpnicfNSHostIPAddr.description: The destination IP address of the exported packet. This destination IP address is a NSC (NS Collector) address.

hpnicfNSHostPort.name: hpnicfNSHostPort
hpnicfNSHostPort.description: The destination port of the exported packets. This destination port is a NSC listening port.

hpnicfNSSrcIpAddr.name: hpnicfNSSrcIpAddr
hpnicfNSSrcIpAddr.description: The source IP address of the exported packets.

hpnicfNSState.name: hpnicfNSState
hpnicfNSState.description: The state of aggregation is enabled or disabled.

hpnicfNSExportInformationTable.name: hpnicfNSExportInformationTable
hpnicfNSExportInformationTable.description: This table describes the Information of the exported packets.

hpnicfNSExportType.name: hpnicfNSExportType
hpnicfNSExportType.description: This object is equal to hpnicfNSAggregationType.

hpnicfNSExportSlot.name: hpnicfNSExportSlot
hpnicfNSExportSlot.description: This object is equal to hpnicfNSProcessSlot.

hpnicfNSExportStream.name: hpnicfNSExportStream
hpnicfNSExportStream.description: This object counts the exported streams.

hpnicfNSExportNum.name: hpnicfNSExportNum
hpnicfNSExportNum.description: This object counts the exported packets.

hpnicfNSExportFail.name: hpnicfNSExportFail
hpnicfNSExportFail.description: This object counts the exported packets which failed to send. The error may be unreachable destination IP address.

hpnicfNSSourceSlot.name: hpnicfNSSourceSlot
hpnicfNSSourceSlot.description: The IP packet will be counted when it is passing through this slot.

hpnicfNSSourceIfIndex.name: hpnicfNSSourceIfIndex
hpnicfNSSourceIfIndex.description: The IP packet will be statistics when it through this interface. This object is equal to ifIndex at ifTable.

hpnicfNSDestSlot.name: hpnicfNSDestSlot
hpnicfNSDestSlot.description: This object is equal to hpnicfNSProcessSlot.

hpnicfNSDirect.name: hpnicfNSDirect
hpnicfNSDirect.description: This object describes which packets will be counted. It may be inbound or outbound packets through this interface.

hpnicfNSConfigRowStatus.name: hpnicfNSConfigRowStatus
hpnicfNSConfigRowStatus.description: SNMP Row Status Variable. Writable objects in the table may be written in any RowStatus state.

hpnicfNSStatusTable.name: hpnicfNSStatusTable
hpnicfNSStatusTable.description: This table describes current information of network traffic.

hpnicfNSSlot.name: hpnicfNSSlot
hpnicfNSSlot.description: This object is equal to hpnicfNSProcessSlot.

hpnicfNSActiveStreamNumber.name: hpnicfNSActiveStreamNumber
hpnicfNSActiveStreamNumber.description: This object counts current active streams.

hpnicfNSTotalStreamNumber.name: hpnicfNSTotalStreamNumber
hpnicfNSTotalStreamNumber.description: This object counts all statistic streams.

hpnicfNSTotalPacketNumber.name: hpnicfNSTotalPacketNumber
hpnicfNSTotalPacketNumber.description: This object counts all statistic packets.

hpnicfNSTotalOctetNumber.name: hpnicfNSTotalOctetNumber
hpnicfNSTotalOctetNumber.description: This object counts all statistic octets.

hpnicfNSMPLSActiveStreamNumber.name: hpnicfNSMPLSActiveStreamNumber
hpnicfNSMPLSActiveStreamNumber.description: This object counts current active MPLS streams.

hpnicfNSMPLSTotalStreamNumber.name: hpnicfNSMPLSTotalStreamNumber
hpnicfNSMPLSTotalStreamNumber.description: This object counts all statistic MPLS streams.

hpnicfNSMPLSTotalPacketNumber.name: hpnicfNSMPLSTotalPacketNumber
hpnicfNSMPLSTotalPacketNumber.description: This object counts all statistic MPLS packets.

hpnicfNSMPLSTotalOctetNumber.name: hpnicfNSMPLSTotalOctetNumber
hpnicfNSMPLSTotalOctetNumber.description: This object counts all statistic octets of MPLS packets.

hpnicfNSResetFlag.name: hpnicfNSResetFlag
hpnicfNSResetFlag.description: Reset all streams. The default value is disabled, and set this value to enabled when resetting.

hpnicfNSResetTime.name: hpnicfNSResetTime
hpnicfNSResetTime.description: The system up time when stream is reset.
